.cs 3 on
.item 'SHOW BBOARD Command' 'Updated on 03/27/97 by JNK'
.* Pseudo command
.boxon
SHOW BBOARD [newsgroup|SUMMARY|LIST|DIRECTORY\[LIKE\prefix]]
            [collect-options]
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
This command is obsolete effective Monday, March 31, 1997.

The SHOW BBOARD command displays the posted messages to an electronic bulletin
board, which can be local, national, or international.  If you are issuing the
command for the first time, a newsgroup subscription list will be created and
saved on your account.  The command SHOW BBOARD LIST displays a list of the
newsgroups to which you have subscribed.  Type HELP SET BBOARD for information
on changing your subscription.  Type HELP POST for details on posting items.

Type SHOW BBOARD DIRECTORY to see a list of available newsgroups.  Use the
LIKE option to show newsgroups beginning with the specified string:  SHOW
BBOARD DIR LIKE SDC.

.* SELECT 'SHOW BBOARD Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION NEWSGROUP
.optix newsgroup
newsgroup\\\\\\\display the posted messages from the specified electronic
                bulletin board (newsgroup).

.* OPTION SUMMARY
.optix SUMMARY
SUMMARY\\\\\\\\\display only a summary of newsgroups with unread articles,
                then return to WYLBUR.

.* OPTION LIST
.optix LIST
LIST\\\\\\\\\\\\display the newsgroups to which you have subscribed.  To add
                or delete newsgroups from your subscription list, use the SET
                BBOARD command; type HELP SET BBOARD for more information.

.* OPTION DIRECTORY,LIKE
.optix DIRECTORY
.optix LIKE
DIRECTORY [LIKE\prefix]
\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\DIRECTORY displays the list of available newsgroups (currently
                over 400).  collect-options are often specified with this
                option as the list is quite long.

\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\LIKE displays the newsgroups with the specified prefix.  The
                most common prefixes for newsgroups are:

                   SDC.  -- Stanford Data Center bulletin boards
                   SU.   -- Stanford University bulletin boards
                   BA.   -- Bay Area bulletin boards
                   COMP. -- National and international bulletin boards on the
                            subject of computers and their uses
                   SCI.  -- National and international bulletin boards on the
                            subject of various scientific topics
                   REC.  -- National and international bulletin boards on the
                            subject of "recreational" topics
                   SOC.  -- National and international bulletin boards on the
                            subject of "social" topics

.* OPTION COLLECT-OPTIONS,BY,KEEP,NOCLEAR,NOCLR,CLEAR,CLR,WARN,NOWARN
.optix collect-options
collect-options\allow you to insert the system response to the SHOW BBOARD
                DIRECTORY command into your active file.  Type HELP
                COLLECT-OPTIONS for a description of these options.
.cs 3 off
